UNDIAGNOSED ILLNESS - ALGERIA: (CHLEF) TOXIC ALGAE SUSPECTED
************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 5 Jul 2021
Source: Echorouk online [in Arabic, machine trans., edited]
https://www.echoroukonline.com/etrange-incident-sur-une-plage-de-tenes-149-personnes-evacuees


A media news article reported that the wali (governor) of (the state/wilaya of) Chlef, Lakhdar Sadas, said the accident in which 149 citizens were poisoned on [Tenes] Beach was due to (a leaked) gas, emitted from one of the ships, hitting their respiratory systems.

In a statement to Al-Shorouk News channel, the state's governor confirmed the issue was related to a gas hitting the respiratory system, noting that suspicions were hovering around a ship carrying cattle docked in the port of Chlef.

The same spokesman explained that Public Prosecution was notified of the incident, and the competent authorities began their investigations and sent samples to the capital's laboratories to conduct the necessary analysis; the result is pending. [We are not told what samples were collected or what tests were requested. - Mod.TG]

For reference, the details of the incident date back to Sunday (4 Jul 2021) evening, when 149 citizens who were on [Tenes] Beach were poisoned. Those concerned suffered from nausea, fever, and redness in the eyes, so they were transferred to the Martyr Zigoud Youssef Hospital in [Tenes].

Among the affected are 28 divers and 7 civil protection agents, and the governor confirmed about 50 injured people had left the hospital.

As a precaution, the state's authorities ordered the closure of the 3 beaches [near Tenes], as well as the sea desalination plant in Mainis.

